        "description": "Announcement schedule in five-field UTC cron format (minute hour day-of-month month day-of-week). For common routines, pick one of the preset UTC schedules above. Use a custom expression only when you need something more specific. Matching is always evaluated in UTC because the module compares against getUTC* values. Common examples: */15 * * * * = every 15 minutes, 0 * * * * = at the top of every UTC hour, 30 18 * * 1-5 = 18:30 UTC on weekdays. To avoid timezone mistakes, first decide the UTC wall-clock time you want on the server, then enter that UTC time here: for example 09:00 New York is usually 14:00 UTC in winter and 13:00 UTC in summer, while 09:00 Berlin is usually 08:00 UTC in winter and 07:00 UTC in summer. Re-check the UTC value whenever daylight saving rules change. The module polls every minute and only broadcasts on ticks that match this expression."
